18 treatment or the after-effects of the medical treatment result in any injury, including physical, psychological,
19 emotional, or physiological harms.
20 (2) (a) Except as provided in subsection (3), a person who was a minor at the time the medical
21 treatments listed in subsection (4) were provided to the person and who suffers an injury described in
22 subsection (1) or the person's legal guardian or estate may bring a civil action with respect to the injury within
23 25 years from AT ANY TIME UNTIL 2 YEARS AFTER THE PERSON REACHES THE AGE OF 30 OR UNTIL WITHIN 2 YEARS
