18 system that at some point produces, transports, and utilizes the large gamete, or ova, for fertilization.
19 (b) "Gender" means the psychological, behavioral, social, and cultural aspects of being male or
20 female, when the term is used alone to refer to a male, female, or the natural differences between a male and
21 female:
22 (i) may not be considered a synonym for sex;
23 (ii) may not be considered a synonym or short-hand expression for gender identity, experienced
24 gender, gender expression, or gender role; and
25 (iii) does not apply when it is used in conjunction with other words or as an adjective to modify
26 other words, or when context or explicit definition in preexisting state law, administrative rules, or guidelines
27 indicate otherwise.
